[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I have a question about the following function : </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Create a new GEM object.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Driver</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">size</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">try_pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Opaque</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">drm_gem_object</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">default</span><span class=\"p\">()),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">size</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">GFP_KERNEL</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: `obj.as_raw()` is guaranteed to be valid by the initialization above.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">funcs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">OBJECT_FUNCS</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: The arguments are all valid per the type invariants.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">to_result</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">drm_gem_object_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">size</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: We never move out of `Self`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_inner_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: `ptr` comes from `KBox::into_raw` and hence can't be NULL.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NonNull</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: We take over the initial reference count from `drm_gem_object_init()`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ARef</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>How can we guarantee that we will never move out of Self ? Is this a property of ARef&lt;T&gt; ? I feel that we are losing the fact that Self was pinned since its init when ARef&lt;Self&gt; is returned</p>",
        "id": 565380198,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766679383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ARef is pinned</p>",
        "id": 565380272,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766679509
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right thanks !</p>\n<p>Maybe adding that ARef provide the pinning guarentee in the safety comment of <code>Pin::into_inner_unchecked</code> would make sense then.</p>",
        "id": 565380592,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766680079
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or maybe we can add a method to convert from a<code>Pin&lt;KBox&lt;T&gt;&gt; where T: AlwaysRefCounted</code> to <code>ARef&lt;T&gt;</code> because this is ultimately what the 3 last unsafe lines does</p>",
        "id": 565380659,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766680257
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I guess this can not be easily generalizedbecause of the callback needed to convert back to a <code>KBox</code> when putting the last reference</p>",
        "id": 565380906,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766680654
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>having a safe <code>Pin&lt;KBox&lt;T&gt;&gt;</code> to <code>ARef&lt;T&gt;</code> conversion function sounds like a good idea</p>",
        "id": 565382748,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1766683394
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>though we'd need to ensure that the refcount already is exactly 1 at that point, which in this case is done by <code>drm_gem_object_init</code>, so we'd still need to make the function unsafe</p>",
        "id": 565382816,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1766683469
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It cannot possibly be a safe conversion.</p>",
        "id": 565382834,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766683497
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, having a <code>KBox&lt;T&gt;</code> to an <code>AlwaysRefcounted</code> isn't sound to begin with. Such values cannot escape into arbitrary user code.</p>",
        "id": 565382868,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766683543
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>did you mean \"must not\" instead of \"cannot\"?</p>",
        "id": 565382891,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1766683584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suppose</p>",
        "id": 565382962,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766683703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Another problem is the handling of the deallocation when the refcount reaches 0. In the case of <code>drm_gem_object</code> there is a callback function to let the rust code convert the last reference back to a <code>KBox</code> so it can be properly dropped. I don't know if this behavior can be generalized in a nice way</p>",
        "id": 565383003,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766683773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fundamentally, the goal of <code>AlwaysRefcounted</code> is to handle the long list of special cases that can't be generalized in a nice way.</p>",
        "id": 565383048,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766683835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Of having such a <code>KBox</code> isn't sound, shouldn't <code>ARef</code> provide the way to perform the first allocation ?</p>",
        "id": 565383119,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766683926
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why? What the code does is perfectly fine. The KBox isn't part of the public API of <code>drm::Object</code>.</p>",
        "id": 565383451,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766684464
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Normally, the first allocation is carried out by C code.</p>",
        "id": 565383461,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766684477
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using a KBox here is a bit of a special case.</p>",
        "id": 565383468,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766684484
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To conclude on this, I think the safety comment when unwrapping from <code>Pin</code> can be improved. I can submit a patch on this unless the code is expected to change soon with another patch set if you think it is relevant</p>",
        "id": 565385604,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewan Chorynski",
        "timestamp": 1766687622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that makes sense; feel free.</p>",
        "id": 565385840,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1766688070
    }
]